<h2>Import guests from CSV file</h2>
<p>Your CSV file must contain all guests with the following attributes in the following order:</p>
<ul>
  <li>first name</li>
  <li>last name</li>
  <li>email</li>
  <li>group</li>
  <li>type</li>
</ul>
<p>If you don't want to make use of a certain column, please provide a blank or nil value in that position for each guest.</p>

<p><strong>MAKE SURE</strong> that you include a header row in your CSV file.</p>

<form id="import" action="/process" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
  <p><input type="file" name="file" id="file"></p>
  <p><input type="submit" value="Import"></p>
</form>

<hr />

<h2>Reset the database</h2>
<p>Clicking the button below will erase all records from the database.</p>
<p><strong>MAKE SURE</strong> this is really what you want to do because it can't be undone.</p>

<form id="reset" action="/reset_db" method="post">
  <p><input type="submit" value="Reset Database"></p>
</form>